North Korea Refuses Unilateral Disarmament Without Confidence
North Korea's foreign minister told the United Nations on Saturday that maintaining sanctions was escalating the country's distrust of the United States, which in such circumstances would absolutely refuse to unilaterally give up its nuclear weapons.
